AGI - An infirmary mob lynched a woman suspected of killing an eight-year-old girl in Taxco, South Mexico City. Two more men, suspected of being involved in the same crime, were brutally beaten and are now admitted. Camila disappeared last Wednesday after she went to a house in the neighborhood to use the pool. The mother turned to the police a few hours later, claiming they had received telephone messages asking for a ransom to release her.
&nbsp;
The woman claimed to have provided the security camera agents with another neighbor showing the house where the baby was, but the cops ignored her demands to act.
&nbsp;
Camila's body was found on Thursday. A crowd gathered in front of the house where a woman and two men, under investigation for aggravated murder, dragged them out and hard beaten: the woman died and the two men were hospitalized.&nbsp;

